The latest native run (`v1-native-byte-transformer-20260408-003604`) has formatting solved (`valid_output_rate = 1.0`), and the main remaining error mode is the `CLARIFICATION` vs `DIRECT_ANSWER` boundary. The biggest miss cluster was vague evaluative prompts like â€œIs this enough?â€, â€œShould I wait?â€, and â€œWould this work?â€ being classified as `DIRECT_ANSWER`, so I made one narrow dataset change: I added six seed `CLARIFICATION` examples that reinforce incomplete judgment/fit/choice questions as clarification cases, then rebuilt the processed splits and SFT JSONL so the next training run uses them immediately.

This keeps the experiment comparable and avoids retrying class-balanced loss. After regeneration, the cleaned dataset moved from 93 to 98 `CLARIFICATION` records, and the train split is now 533 rows with 72 `CLARIFICATION` examples.

